1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
DataFinOps connects real requirements to pricing, entitlement, governance, and reproducible savings evidence.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:48,000
The sandbox verifies network, program, pricing, subscription, and API entitlement. The wallet remains a public reference only.

3
00:00:48,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Aggregate usage maps to products, while unallocated spend stays visible. Hard requirements remain separate from preferences.

4
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Every input is frozen. A deterministic optimizer proposes valid configurations, and an independent verifier checks every hard constraint.

5
00:01:48,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Adding a hard fixture creates a new snapshot and recommendation. The requirement is never silently relaxed, and prior evidence remains replayable.

6
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Procurement and finance approve the exact proposal hash under separate roles. Material change invalidates approval.

7
00:02:46,000 --> 00:03:17,000
The unsigned summary binds network, program, changes, amount, expiry, and hashes. The client-side demo signer uses no private-key input or funded transaction.

8
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Confirmation, activation, and effective entitlement are verified separately. Duplicate callbacks never create a second purchase.

9
00:03:47,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Only a complete, verified period can label the synthetic delta realized. Corrections append reversals without rewriting history.

10
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Optimize cost, preserve coverage, and verify value. That is DataFinOps.
